The '''Agua Caliente Casino''' is an Indian-gaming facility in [[Rancho Mirage, California]]. It is run by the Agua Caliente Band of [[Cahuilla]] Indians. The facility currently has over {{convert|45000|sqft|m2}} of gambling floor. The casino is currently building a 16-story, {{convert|173|ft|m|sing=on}} hotel tower than is set to be complete in December 2007. When completed it will be the second tallest building in the [[Inland Empire (California)|Inland Empire]].

The tribe also runs the [[Spa Resort and Casino]] in nearby [[Palm Springs, California]].

